    "Geographically, 9 countries have been represented, where China is predominantly the most productive with 19 Papers followed distantly by the USA with 7 papers, India with 3 papers, Indonesia and Germany with 2 papers, and finally the UK, Sweden, Italy, Saudi Arabia, and Australia with one paper each as illustrated in Fig. 4.",
    "What are the Use Cases and Targeted stakeholders of Blockchain in the Sports Industry?For the sake of answering the first research question, we have coded our resource poll (n = 38) based on the following characteristics: type of paper, the field of sports, the proposed use case, and the targeted stakeholder, as shown in Table 6.",
    "Type of PapersFor the type of paper, we have identified two broad types; reports and technical papers.",
    "Reports refer to papers that discuss the use of blockchain in the sports industry in a broad way; giving examples and ideas without any technical contributions or implementations.",
